name: places/ChIJby_OmM9RqEcRAkdmpR-FbBY
editorialSummary.text: Busy counter-serve restaurant turning out Turkish classics, plus burgers & vegetarian options.
reviews[0].name: places/ChIJby_OmM9RqEcRAkdmpR-FbBY/reviews/ChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnTUN3MTliMzN3RRAB
reviews[0].text.text:
This was a legitimately great spot for authentic Turkish food. Despite being very close to the heart of tourist Berlin, there is nothing fake about this place.

We ordered from the grilled kebab menu. Chicken skewers were moist, seasoned and with a generous portion of rice and salad. I got the lamb-veal skewer, on a bed of grilled flatbread and yogurt. Insanely delicious.

reviews[2].text.text:
Everything was delicious until I found trash in my kebab. After that, I completely lost my appetite, threw the kebab away, and felt nauseous all day from what I had seen. The dish is quite pricey, but I’m willing to pay if the food is of good quality. To be honest, I never expected such negligence when it comes to food—allowing trash in it is unacceptable.

It was also clear how the staff worked—none of them were particularly friendly. I was just a regular visitor, and I left the café angry, knowing that no one would refund me for this.

editorialSummary.text: Classic Berlin food in a plush, old-world brasserie setting with frosted glass, plus a terrace.
reviews[0].name: places/ChIJ5xaQvsRRqEcRN8-Wy6L3dEE/reviews/ChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnTUN3d0lPX0dREAE
reviews[0].text.text: The food and the service were phenomenal. I had traditional sausage with cabbage, my husband had the soups and variety of sausages. We finished the dinner with a cup of three scoops of ice cream and apple strudel. Everything was just perfect. Our waiter spoke English and was very nice and attentive. Portions were good and the price were fair. We love this place and definitely will recommend.

reviews[1].text.text:
The food is, spectacular. I had calf liver, apple strudel with whip cream and ice cream for dessert. A glass of Österreich Austrian red wine and an espresso.

Liver with mash potato's and gravy was totally delicious specially the sauce and the meat was perfectly cooked.

Apple strudel freshly made it and the ice cream is delicious.

About the wine, one of the best I have ever had.

Espresso also one of the bests I drink in a restaurant.

More and more importantly service is amazing. Waiters are very friendly and professional. Totally 10/10. I will be back in my next visit in Berlin.

editorialSummary.text: Japanese restaurant with wood flooring serving sushi, fresh fish & seasonal vegetable-based fare.
reviews[0].name: places/ChIJXZ4AgcRRqEcRzwjWx_mEBAY/reviews/ChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnTUN3c29MOEh3EAE
reviews[0].text.text: It’s definitely 5 for price/performance ratio. It is so much better than all the classic sushi restaurants you can find it in Berlin(excluding the high end ones). Service is super fast, and sushi is super fresh. We went there around 17.30-18.00 in a weekday and it was pretty crowded. At 18.30 there was a long queue in front of the door.

reviews[1].name: places/ChIJXZ4AgcRRqEcRzwjWx_mEBAY/reviews/ChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSURIdG96U3hBRRAB
reviews[1].text.text:
If you want to try authentic Japanese food, this place will be the best for that kind of experience. This place reminds me of a typical Japanese fast food place with quality products, very fast work and friendly waiters.
The big plus point of the place is the speed of preparation and the taste of the food. Also, the food here is quite hearty. It may seem like you won't get full, but actually even a small set of sushi rolls is quite hearty.
The average price is more than affordable, especially for Japanese food. You can order a set for €10-18 and you don't need to take drinks because the green tea is free.

My fav is their Negitoro Don ❤️

reviews[3].text.text:
Ishin a fantastic sushi restaurant, where you can enjoy authentic sushi at a very reasonable price. It’s such a great find to have high-quality sushi that’s both delicious and affordable. I found myself visiting almost every week, as the food is consistently excellent.
The service is also outstanding friendly and attentive, making each visit even more enjoyable. If you’re in Berlin and craving sushi, Ishin is definitely a place you shouldn’t miss!

reviews[4].text.text:
Ishin Sushi in Berlin is the definition of “it’s fine” when it comes to sushi. The taste is okay, but don’t expect to be blown away—it’s pretty basic. The sushi is fresh and decent, but nothing that’s going to have you running back for more. If you’re looking for super unique flavors or a next-level experience, this might not be your spot.

That said, the prices are super reasonable, especially for Berlin. It’s one of the cheaper sushi places around, so if you’re ballin’ on a budget, Ishin gets the job done. Plus, they give you free green tea, which is always a win.

reviews[0].text.text:
I recently visited this restaurant for a weekend lunch based on a recommendation, and it turned out to be an excellent choice for vegan food lovers. The place has a cozy ambiance with both indoor and outdoor seating options, making it a comfortable dining spot.

We started with a seasonal appetizer, which was fresh and flavorful. For the main course, we ordered the Tonkatsu Curry and a ramen dish—both were delicious and well-prepared. The portion sizes were just right, offering a satisfying meal without being overwhelming.

The staff was friendly and attentive, enhancing the overall dining experience. If you're looking for a great vegan-friendly restaurant with tasty food and a welcoming atmosphere, this is definitely worth a visit!

reviews[1].text.text:
We completely lucked out by this place being round the corner from our accommodation when we visited Berlin.

The service was very quick, the food was incredible, the drinks were delicious and the saki was such a treat. I took two non vegans here and they both absolutely loved it too, my partner is a chef and can be really particular about food but had absolutely nothing but positive things to say about the whole meal.
Between the three of us we tried three different mains and almost all the sides and everything was delicious, highly recommend!

Would advise booking a table to avoid disappointment as it was busy which is also a good sign!

reviews[3].text.text:
Interesting vegan food.
We found the place by chance but enjoyed it very much.
We took 3 business lunches, which included a main course and the glass of tea. We started with the beetroot gyoza, which was good but a beet bland. For the main course, we tried 2 ramen , chicken and beef, and one curry. All good, but the curry was definitely the best with a lot of flavours, some of some new to me.
For dessert, we took a mochi, which was full of mango flavour on the inside.
Something different and tasty.

Worth it!

Luckily we didn’t need a reservation but the place was very busy so would recommend booking to avoid disappointment if you’re in a group.

reviews[0].text.text:
A very nice place with very fast and polite service.
We went for breakfast and arrived 5 minutes before opening time and, despite the cold weather, they didn't let us in to wait inside for them to finish preparing.
The service from the waiters was very good and the food was delicious.
The menu is not very long, but the portion sizes are large and you will be full. Good quality/price ratio.

reviews[2].text.text: Really neat restaurant that has some tasty vegan breakfast options! I tried the vegan hot chocolate (super excited to try this as I've never had it in the vegan form) with a vegan raspberry croissant, along with their avocado toast and a side of vegan eggs. The hot chocolate was delicious and the pastry was very soft. The avocado toast was severed on a hefty piece of bread that filled me up pretty quickly. The eggs however were a little disappointing, but was not expecting them to be great to begin with giving my past experiences eating vegan eggs. The staff was super friendly and service was quick. Would highly recommend stopping in for a bite on your way to see the Berlin gate not too far away from here too.
